                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Conger</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-08-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 23, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Adee states that the consul-general at Shanghai has been telegraphed that he
                    is not to commit himself to any theory that the United States could be called
                    upon by China or by the foreign consuls to guarantee Chinese neutrality, and
                    that he is to safeguard only as far as possible xlmerican neutral interests if
                    threatened, and to avoid all indications of general policy. Utmost
                    circumspection required.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
